Title: 10 Reasons Startups Prefer Node.js over .NET
Description: I’ve been a .NET software developer for my entire career, and I truly love the platform. I love the C# language, the productivity of the platform, and the ecosystem. But I’ve been dealing with an existential crisis for years now. I see how companies, especially startups, don’t seem to choose .NET as their platform of choice. They go to Node.js, Ruby, Python, or even Java as an alternative to ASP.NET. I even went as far as to write an article about it: Where did the Microsoft Tech Stack disappear?

Title: Community Event Signup
Description: .NET Conf is a FREE, three-day, virtual developer event that celebrates the major releases of the .NET development platform. It is co-organized by the .NET community and Microsoft, and sponsored by the .NET Foundation along with our ecosystem partners. Organize a watch party and/or post-conference presentation for your community or Meetup group and get all the technical content, promotion, and SWAG needed to create your event. Your event can be virtual or in-person depending on your local area health guidelines.If you plan to host an in-person watch party or event in a city with a Microsoft Reactor location, we can connect you with the Reactor space to serve as your venue.The .NET Conf team will provide the following for Hosts organizing events happening from November 8, 2022 through January 31, 2023:- Promotion of your event through #dotnetconf hashtag. - Promotion of your event on the .NET Conf local events page (https://dotnetconf.net).  - Technical content and a hands-on workshop. - Artwork to present and promote your local group/s. - SWAG for you and your attendees! How to Participate:- Coordinate a .NET Conf 2022 event for your local community or Meetup group. - Title your event with ".NET Conf 2022 [Name of your community group/location]". *Note: This form allows the request of both speakers and streaming support for virtual .NET Conf 2022 events. These are limited resources and provided based on support team availability on a “first-come-first-served" basis. Thus, we cannot guarantee every speaker and streaming request submitted for virtual events.
